# ez-text2video

<p align="center">
  <img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/115115916/229304939-077368d0-58a2-499e-a2c8-010e1bb5f4e7.png" alt="App screenshot" width="720" />
</p>

Streamlit UI for the [ModelScope text-to-video](https://huggingface.co/damo-vilab/text-to-video-ms-1.7b) weights in Diffusers. Runs on NVIDIA CUDA (including modest VRAM with offload), Apple Silicon (MPS), or CPU.

**Stack:** [Diffusers](https://github.com/huggingface/diffusers), [PyTorch](https://pytorch.org/), [Streamlit](https://streamlit.io/).

Layout:

```text
<repo-root>/
  pyproject.toml
  requirements.txt
  README.md
  tests/
  ez-text2video/
    app.py
    lib/
    environment.yaml
```

The **repository root** holds packaging, tests, and CI. The **Streamlit app** and **`lib` package** live under `ez-text2video/`.

---

## Prerequisites

| Item | Notes |
|------|--------|
| **Python** | 3.10 or 3.11 |
| **Git** | [git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/downloads) |
| **PyTorch** | Install a build that matches your OS and device: [Get started locally](https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/). |
| **CUDA (optional)** | For NVIDIA GPUs: [CUDA Toolkit](https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads) aligned with your PyTorch build. |
| **Conda (optional)** | [Miniconda](https://docs.conda.io/en/latest/miniconda.html) if you use `environment.yaml`. |

**Model weights** download automatically on first run from Hugging Face into `ez-text2video/cache/` (several GB). Model terms: [model card](https://huggingface.co/damo-vilab/text-to-video-ms-1.7b).

---

## Install

### Option A — Conda

Use the **repository root** (the folder that contains `pyproject.toml` and the `ez-text2video/` subdirectory):

```bash
git clone https://github.com/kpthedev/ez-text2video.git
cd ez-text2video
conda env create -f ez-text2video/environment.yaml
conda activate t2v
```

The first `cd` is into your **clone directory** (often named like the GitHub repo). The file path `ez-text2video/environment.yaml` is always relative to that root.

### Option B — venv + pip

From the same repository root:

```bash
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate          # Windows
# source .venv/bin/activate     # Linux / macOS
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install torch --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu124   # example: CUDA 12.4; adjust at pytorch.org
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Use the CPU index URL from [pytorch.org](https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/) if you do not need a GPU build.

---

## Run

From the **repository root**:

```bash
streamlit run ez-text2video/app.py
```

Or `cd` into the app directory, then:

```bash
cd ez-text2video
streamlit run app.py
```

Optional device override (after `--`):

```bash
streamlit run ez-text2video/app.py -- --device cuda    # cuda | mps | cpu
```

Generated WebM files are written under `ez-text2video/outputs/`.

---

## Development

From the **repository root** (where `pyproject.toml` and `tests/` are):

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"
ruff check .
ruff format .
pytest
```

---

## Deployment

### Docker (CPU image)

Build from the **repository root**:

```bash
docker build -t ez-text2video .
docker run --rm -p 8501:8501 ez-text2video
```

Browse to `http://localhost:8501`. For production, put TLS and auth in front of the container. GPU hosts need a CUDA base image and the matching `torch` wheel from [PyTorch](https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/); this Dockerfile is intentionally CPU-only.

### Streamlit Community Cloud

Set the main file to **`ez-text2video/app.py`**, Python **3.10**, and install dependencies from the root **`requirements.txt`**. Free-tier resources are limited; this model is heavy without a large machine or GPU-backed hosting.

